Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti. Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10g} and @ground cumin{1%tsp} into a #bowl{}. Add the @water{1.5%tbsp} for the meatballs and mix together. Add the @British beef mince{480%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using your hands, mix everything together until very well combined. Form the mixture into evenly sized balls, 4 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned all over, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: Do this in batches if necessary, you want the meatballs to brown not stew!

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Once the meatballs are cooked, transfer to a #plate{} then drain any remaining fat out of the pan. Add the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} to the pan along with half of the @harissa paste{50%g}, stir well and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(chopped), and @water{100%ml}.

Add the @beef stock paste{10%g}, and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to the boil, simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{9-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when the water for the pasta is boiling, add the @spaghetti{180%g} and cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has cooked, set aside 2 meatballs per wrap. Pop the remaining meatballs into the tomato sauce and heat until the meatballs are piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Finally, add the drained spaghetti into the sauce and mix well. Serve in #bowls{} with a sprinkle of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and enjoy!

When you're ready to pack your lunch, pop the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and leftover harissa paste into a #small bowl{}, mix to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto a #board{}, divide the reserved meatballs between wraps, add baby gem and the yoghurt mixture. Wrap in #foil{} and refrigerate. At lunchtime, enjoy cold.

> For ultimate freshness, keep the fillings separate and assemble when you are ready to eat them. Enjoy.